class ListNode {
    constructor(val, next = null) {
        this.val = val;
        this.next = next;
    }
}

function deleteMiddle(head) {
    if (!head || !head.next) return head;
    let slow = head;
    let fast = head;
    let prev = null;

    while (fast && fast.next) {
        prev = slow;
        slow = slow.next;
        fast = fast.next.next;
    }

    prev.next = slow.next;
    return head;
}
```


    The algorithm utilizes the slow and fast pointer approach to find the middle node of the linked list. Initialize two pointers: slow and fast both pointing to the head of the list. Additionally, have a prev pointer to store the previous node of slow pointer.

In each iteration of the while loop, move the slow pointer by one step and fast pointer by two steps. When fast pointer reaches the end of the linked list or there is no next for fast pointer, then the slow pointer points to the middle node.

At each step, update the prev pointer to the current slow pointer, so when we reach the middle node, the prev pointer points to the node before the middle node. Then, update the next attribute of the prev node to skip the middle node (slow->next). Finally, return the head of the modified linked list.

